% Automatisch generiert — Thema: School Uniforms
% arg/1 Fakten
arg(pro82).  % [pro] Uniforms help troubled students feel that troubled students have the support of a community.
arg(pro15).  % [pro] When students are dressed alike, students are safer.
arg(pro4).  % [pro] Students dressed in uniform are better perceived by teachers and peers.
arg(pro95).  % [pro] Former US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton, when she was a 2008 US presidential candidate, advocated school uniforms as a way to help students focus on learning, saying: “Take clothing choices off the table and put the focus on school, not on what students are wearing.”
arg(pro36).  % [pro] Uniforms provide less distraction.
arg(pro36b).  % [pro] Uniforms provide less drama.
arg(pro36c).  % [pro] Uniforms provide more focus on learning.
arg(pro32).  % [pro] It is very important that girls do not have to give in to these sorts of pressures.
arg(pro32b).  % [pro] Girls actually welcome wearing a uniform.
arg(pro29).  % [pro] If someone were to come into a building, the intruder could easily be recognized.
arg(con36).  % [con] Nothing says 'the issue is not just about you' more than an ugly uniform.
arg(con27).  % [con] The school's uniform policy broke the guarantee of a free public education.
arg(con27b).  % [con] The school's uniform policy violated children's right to freedom of expression.
arg(con27c).  % [con] The parents were required to pay $641 for their children's uniforms in August 2007.
arg(con140).  % [con] Most public schools with uniform policies are located in poor neighborhoods.
arg(con140b).  % [con] Uniform policies emphasize the class distinctions that uniforms were supposed to eliminate.
arg(con23).  % [con] The paper titled “Public School Uniforms: Effect on Perceptions of Gang Presence, School Climate, and Student Self-Perceptions” shows that students who are not required to wear school uniforms demonstrated higher self-perception scores.
arg(con109).  % [con] However, serious discipline and academic issues are unlikely to be solved by nostalgically resurrecting the blazer or draconian decrees issued from the headmaster's study regarding skirt length.
arg(con9).  % [con] A student's transition towards adulthood can be hindered by uniforms.
arg(con8).  % [con] There are limited choices for males.
arg(con8b).  % [con] There are limited choices for females.

% att/2 Fakten  (Dung 1995 — binär; Typ/conf aus LLM-Kandidaten als Kommentar)
att(con36, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=80 — The con claim that an ugly uniform highlights individual issues challenges the premise that uniforms foster community support for troubled students.
att(con27, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=70 — Con argues the policy is illegal, undermining the legitimacy of any claimed community support.
att(con27b, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=75 — Con claims the policy violates freedom of expression, challenging the premise that uniforms can positively support students.
att(con27c, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=80 — Con highlights high uniform costs, suggesting the policy may hinder rather than help troubled students.
att(con140b, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=80 — Con asserts uniforms emphasize class distinctions, contradicting the idea they foster community support.
att(con23, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=90 — Con cites research showing higher self‑perception without uniforms, directly refuting the support claim.
att(con109, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=85 — Con argues uniforms cannot solve serious discipline or academic issues, challenging the claimed benefit for troubled students.
att(con9, pro82).  % [NONE] conf=80 — Con states uniforms hinder transition to adulthood, opposing the notion they provide supportive community feelings.
att(con140, pro15).  % [NONE] conf=70 — Pointing out that most uniform schools are in poor neighborhoods suggests safety may be due to socioeconomic factors, undermining the claim that uniforms cause safety.
att(pro32, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=70 — The claim that girls should avoid pressure implies uniforms are a pressure, contradicting the idea that they improve perception
att(con36, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=80 — Calling uniforms 'ugly' undermines the claim that they lead to better perception
att(con140b, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=80 — B argues uniforms reinforce class distinctions, undermining A's premise that uniforms improve perception.
att(con23, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=90 — B cites evidence that non‑uniformed students have higher self‑perception, directly contradicting A's claim.
att(con9, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=70 — B claims uniforms hinder adulthood transition, challenging the positive perception asserted by A.
